Ing '''Mariveles''' metung yang primerung klasing  [[Philippine municipality|balen]] king  [[Philippine province|lalawigan]] ning [[Bataan province|Bataan]], [[Filipinas]]. Agpang keng [[2000]] sensus, atin yang papulasyun a 85,779 a katau ka reng  19,460 a pamimalemale.

==Bataan Timawang Libayan a Labuad==

Ing Mariveles ya ing karinan ning Bataan Timawang Libayan a Labuad (Bataan Free Trade Zone) (FTZ), nung nu la reng subcontractors a mangawang malan at sapatus para ka reng mangaragul a makalipatlipat a corporation. Ing  Mariveles Port mitatag ya bilang Foreign Trade Zone inyang [[1969]], kaibat mipalagyuan a Export Processing Zone (EPZ) inyang [[1995]] [http://www.itcilo.it/english/actrav/telearn/global/ilo/frame/epzppi.htm]. It is, however, commonly referred to as the Bataan FTZ. The Bataan FTZ was the site of massive labor protests in the [[1980s]], as the mostly women workers facing low wages and immiserating working conditions in the factories challenged Philippine laws banning unions in the FTZ. Workers organized in secret and went on strike [http://www.newday.com/films/The_Global_Assembly_Line.html]. After the labor protests, many manufacturers moved out of the Bataan FTZ at Mariveles. Some have returned since then, as working conditions and labor relations have improved over time in the Bataan FTZ in comparison with some other FTZs in the Philippines.

